description: From the verb phrase strike out.

entries.meaning: (countable) An instance or the act of yielding nothing.
examples: We've had one strikeout after the other on the Jones account.

entries.meaning: (countable, baseball) An instance or the act of striking out.
examples: The pitcher recorded seven strikeouts in the game.

entries.meaning: (computing, wordprocessing) Cancellation of a portion of text by crossing it out without deleting it; strikethrough.

verbs.description: strikeout (third-person singular simple present strikeouts, present participle strikeouting, simple past and past participle strikeouted)

entries.meaning: (computing, textprocessing) To cancel a portion of text by crossing it out without deleting it; strikethrough.
